#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:14
msgid "Bend Transform with Clamp ON and OFF"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:16
msgid ""
"This tool rotates a line of selected elements forming an arc between the "
"mouse-cursor and the 3D-cursor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:20
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:22
msgid ""
"The bend tool can be used in any case where you might want to bend a shape "
"in two with a gradual transition between both sides."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:25
msgid ""
"This may take a little getting used to, the basics are listed below controls"
" are noted here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:27
msgid "The initial position of the cursors define the axis to bend on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:28
msgid ""
"The distance of the mouse-cursor to the 3d-cursor controls how sharp the "
"bend will be."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:29
msgid ""
"The relative angle of the mouse-cursor to the initial axis defines the bend "
"angle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:31
msgid ""
"If this seems overly complicated, its probably best to try the tool where it"
" becomes quickly apparent how the tool reacts to your input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:35
msgid "Bend Angle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:35
msgid "The amount of rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:38
msgid "Radius"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:38
msgid "The sharpness of the bend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:46
msgid "Clamp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:41
msgid ""
"Normally the arc turns through a clamped rotation angle with the selected "
"elements extended along a tangent line beyond that (see above left). When "
"the clamp is OFF, the arc continues around aligning the selected elements "
"into a circle (right)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:45
msgid ""
"When OFF (:kbd:`Alt`) all selected elements follow a circle, even when "
"outside the segment between the 3d cursor and the mouse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:50
msgid ""
"Unlike most other transform modes *Bend* isn't effected by *Pivot Point* or "
"*Transform Orientation*, always using the View Plane instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/meshes/editing/deforming/bend.rst:55
msgid ""
"You can turn the bend angle through multiple rotations potentially forming a"
" spiral shape."
msgstr ""
